Drop the uppercase "Thunar" -> "thunar" compatibility symlink.

Thunar installs a capital-T "Thunar" symlink beside the "thunar" binary as a
legacy alias. Tunix is staged and packed on a case-insensitive Windows drvfs
mount, where "Thunar" and "thunar" are the same path -- so meson install aborts
with "Destination '.../usr/bin/Thunar' already exists and is not a symlink" once
the binary is in place. Nothing on Tunix invokes the capital-T name (the desktop
entry uses Exec=thunar), so the alias is simply not installed.

--- a/thunar/meson.build
+++ b/thunar/meson.build
@@ -273,12 +273,6 @@
   install_dir: get_option('prefix') / get_option('datadir') / 'applications',
 )

-install_symlink(
-  'Thunar',
-  install_dir: get_option('prefix') / get_option('bindir'),
-  pointing_to: 'thunar',
-)
-
 install_data(
   'thunar-settings',
   install_dir: get_option('prefix') / get_option('bindir'),
